searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime","doc":"Async trigger dispatch runtime with durable transport-state recovery.","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.execute_result/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.html#t:execute_result/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.runtime_state/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.html#t:runtime_state/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.enqueue/3","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.html#enqueue/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.enqueue/4","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.html#enqueue/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.fetch_dispatch/2","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.html#fetch_dispatch/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.list_dispatches/2","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.html#list_dispatches/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.register_handler/3","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.html#register_handler/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.replay/2","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.html#replay/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Dispatch","doc":"Durable transport-state record for async trigger execution.","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Dispatch.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Dispatch.status/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Dispatch.html#t:status/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Dispatch.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Dispatch.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Dispatch.new!/1","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Dispatch.html#new!/1"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Handler","doc":"Host-controlled trigger handler registration for async dispatch execution.","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Handler.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Handler.context/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Handler.html#t:context/0"},{"type":"callback","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Handler.execution_opts/2","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Handler.html#c:execution_opts/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Telemetry","doc":"Package-owned `:telemetry` surface for async dispatch lifecycle observation.\n\nEvent families:\n\n- `[:jido, :integration, :dispatch_runtime, :enqueue]`\n- `[:jido, :integration, :dispatch_runtime, :deliver]`\n- `[:jido, :integration, :dispatch_runtime, :retry]`\n- `[:jido, :integration, :dispatch_runtime, :dead_letter]`\n- `[:jido, :integration, :dispatch_runtime, :replay]`\n\nMetadata is redacted through `Jido.Integration.V2.Redaction` and remains\nsupplemental to durable control-plane `Event` records.","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Telemetry.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Telemetry.event_name/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Telemetry.html#t:event_name/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Telemetry.emit/3","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Telemetry.html#emit/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Telemetry.event/1","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Telemetry.html#event/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Telemetry.events/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Telemetry.html#events/0"},{"type":"extras","title":"Jido Integration V2 Dispatch Runtime","doc":"# Jido Integration V2 Dispatch Runtime\n\nReusable async trigger runtime above `core/control_plane`.\n\nOwns:\n\n- durable dispatch acceptance\n- explicit trigger-handler registration\n- worker scheduling and execution\n- package-owned `:telemetry` for live async lifecycle observation\n- retry and backoff timing\n- dead-letter transitions and replay\n- recovery of queued or in-flight transport work after runtime restart\n- stable query APIs for current dispatch state\n\nThe package does not recreate a repo-root runtime supervisor. Hosts start and\nname the runtime explicitly where they need it.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"API Surface - Jido Integration V2 Dispatch Runtime","doc":"The runtime exposes:\n\n- `start_link/1`\n- `register_handler/3`\n- `enqueue/3`\n- `enqueue/4`\n- `fetch_dispatch/2`\n- `list_dispatches/2`\n- `replay/2`\n\nHandlers stay explicit and host-controlled through\n`Jido.Integration.V2.DispatchRuntime.Handler`.","ref":"readme.html#api-surface"},{"type":"extras","title":"Minimal Host Flow - Jido Integration V2 Dispatch Runtime","doc":"1. start the runtime with a storage directory\n2. register a handler for the trigger id you expect to execute\n3. admit or fetch a `TriggerRecord`\n4. call `enqueue/3` or `enqueue/4`\n5. inspect state with `fetch_dispatch/2` or `list_dispatches/2`\n6. replay dead-lettered work with `replay/2`\n\nHosted webhook routes typically arrive here from `core/webhook_router` after\n`core/ingress` has admitted the trigger into canonical control-plane truth.","ref":"readme.html#minimal-host-flow"},{"type":"extras","title":"Telemetry - Jido Integration V2 Dispatch Runtime","doc":"This package owns these stable `:telemetry` families:\n\n- `[:jido, :integration, :dispatch_runtime, :enqueue]`\n- `[:jido, :integration, :dispatch_runtime, :deliver]`\n- `[:jido, :integration, :dispatch_runtime, :retry]`\n- `[:jido, :integration, :dispatch_runtime, :dead_letter]`\n- `[:jido, :integration, :dispatch_runtime, :replay]`\n\nMetadata is redacted through `Jido.Integration.V2.Redaction` before emission.\nTelemetry stays supplemental to durable `Event` records in the control plane.","ref":"readme.html#telemetry"},{"type":"extras","title":"Lifecycle - Jido Integration V2 Dispatch Runtime","doc":"1. `enqueue/3` or `enqueue/4` persists a durable dispatch record keyed to the\n   trigger dedupe scope.\n2. The runtime binds that transport record to canonical control-plane truth by\n   calling `ControlPlane.admit_trigger/2` unless the trigger is already bound\n   to a `run_id`.\n3. Once a handler is registered for the trigger id, a worker starts the next\n   dispatch attempt and calls `ControlPlane.execute_run/3`.\n4. Success marks the dispatch completed.\n5. Failures move the dispatch into `:retry_scheduled` with exponential backoff\n   until `max_attempts` is exhausted, then into `:dead_lettered`.\n6. `replay/2` re-queues dead-lettered work so the next attempt number is used.","ref":"readme.html#lifecycle"},{"type":"extras","title":"Pressure Split - Jido Integration V2 Dispatch Runtime","doc":"- `core/policy` may deny or shed work before any attempt exists\n- this package owns backoff timing once work has already been admitted\n- retry telemetry may include `backoff_ms`, but that is scheduler state, not a\n  policy verdict","ref":"readme.html#pressure-split"},{"type":"extras","title":"Recovery Model - Jido Integration V2 Dispatch Runtime","doc":"Dispatch transport state is file-backed by this package, so queued,\nretry-scheduled, and dead-lettered dispatches survive runtime process restarts.\n\nIn-flight work that loses the runtime process is recovered on a new attempt.\nThe earlier control-plane attempt record remains as accepted evidence, and the\nrecovered execution continues on the next deterministic `attempt_id`.\n\nFor full BEAM restart recovery of both transport and control-plane truth, pair\nthis package with durable control-plane stores such as `core/store_local` or\n`core/store_postgres`. With the default in-memory control-plane stores, only\nthe dispatch transport record survives a full application restart.","ref":"readme.html#recovery-model"},{"type":"extras","title":"Proof Surface - Jido Integration V2 Dispatch Runtime","doc":"Current proofs:\n\n- `core/dispatch_runtime/test/jido/integration/v2/dispatch_runtime_test.exs`\n- `apps/devops_incident_response`, which uses this package together with\n  `core/store_local` and `core/webhook_router` to prove dead-letter, replay,\n  and restart recovery","ref":"readme.html#proof-surface"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"}}